RORY MCILROY: Yeah, so I thought if I could get to 4-over, I thought that was two 72s, I thought that would have a good chance.  Especially the forecast looks like the wind is going to die down.  I though we got it pretty windy this morning, and we got it pretty windy yesterday afternoon.
So I'd say that in terms of the scoring between the two sides of the draw, I'd say ours was maybe a shot tougher.  We'll see how that pans out at the end of the day.  I felt like if I could -- I wanted to shoot 3-under on the back nine.  That's what I needed to do.  And I said to Harry going up the 18th, Let's not shoot any worse than I shot yesterday.  So let's make 72 the worst score we're going to shoot.  And it was nice to go one better than that and shoot 1-over in the end.
